            <title>[LU-14771] Rearrange client version warning</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14771</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Trivial change to rearrange the LCONSOLE_WARN message so that the client version isn&apos;t isolated at the end of line, ie from&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; Lustre: Server MGS version (2.5.1.0) is much older than client. Consider upgrading server (2.12.6)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Client version (2.12.6). Server MGS version (2.5.1.0) is much older than client. Consider upgrading server&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve got a local git branch, (cloned from git://git.whamcloud.com/fs/lustre-release.git - I&apos;d fork the github one, but notice that the logs are a couple of weeks behind.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8211; My first patch contribution to whamcloud, can you point me to preferred processes?&lt;br/&gt;
getting internal server errors attaching the 24 line patch&lt;/p&gt;</description>
